				<pubDate>Mon, 20 Oct 2014 16:25:24 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1361261</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's totally fine if this article doesn't work for you. But I feel compelled to point out that this is addressed in the article:</p> <blockquote> <p>Biometric data analysis, voice recognition software and audiovisual manipulation screenings have determined that each SCP-1229 instance is a true and accurate recording of Ms. Neal.</p> </blockquote> <p>I figure if the CIA can authenticate voice recordings and videos of particular individuals, the Foundation probably can as well.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
