					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-554096#post-1766105</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-554096/scp-1229#post-1766105</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 04 May 2013 02:27:55 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>VAElynx</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>914331</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Okay. i read through the SCP - it was written in a way perfectly fitting a document drop, tone and content, and I kinda liked the idea, so I upvoted.<br /> Then came the logs.</p> <blockquote> <p>Segment starts with a card bearing the title &quot;Rats in the Walls&quot;, followed by a short theme song typical of situation comedies from the 1970s.</p> </blockquote> <p>Rats in the Walls. As situational comedy. It's one of the stories I like a lot&#8230; and then the rest of the log, and the following ones. Like the indonesian airlines crash. And I wanted to upvote at least twice more, because despite having background music (was procrastinating from studying) this article *still* managed to creep me out, and few things on this site do that these days.<br /> Friggin' well done.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
